==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cento
<hw>Cen"to</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Centos</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L. <ets>cento</ets> a
garment of several pieces sewed together, patchwork, a poem made up of
various verses of another poem.]</ety> <def>A literary or a musical
composition formed by selections from different authors disposed in a
new order.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Centonism</ent>⟦br⟧
